title: TypeError
markdown:
# TypeError

The **`TypeError`** object represents an error when an operation could not be performed, typically (but not exclusively) when a value is not of the expected type.

A `TypeError` may be thrown when:

* an operand or argument passed to a function is incompatible with the type expected by that operator or function; or
* when attempting to modify a value that cannot be changed; or
* when attempting to use a value in an inappropriate way.

`TypeError` is a [serializable object](/en-US/docs/Glossary/Serializable%5Fobject), so it can be cloned with [structuredClone()](/en-US/docs/Web/API/structuredClone) or copied between [Workers](/en-US/docs/Web/API/Worker) using [postMessage()](/en-US/docs/Web/API/Worker/postMessage "postMessage()").

`TypeError` is a subclass of [Error](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/Error).

## [Constructor](#constructor)

[TypeError()](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/TypeError/TypeError)

Creates a new `TypeError` object.

## [Instance properties](#instance%5Fproperties)

_Also inherits instance properties from its parent [Error](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/Error)_.

These properties are defined on `TypeError.prototype` and shared by all `TypeError` instances.

[TypeError.prototype.constructor](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/Object/constructor)

The constructor function that created the instance object. For `TypeError` instances, the initial value is the [TypeError](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/TypeError/TypeError) constructor.

[TypeError.prototype.name](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/Error/name)

Represents the name for the type of error. For `TypeError.prototype.name`, the initial value is `"TypeError"`.

## [Instance methods](#instance%5Fmethods)

_Inherits instance methods from its parent [Error](/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/Error)_.

## [Examples](#examples)

### [Catching a TypeError](#catching%5Fa%5Ftypeerror)

```
try {
  null.f();
} catch (e) {
  console.log(e instanceof TypeError); // true
  console.log(e.message); // "null has no properties"
  console.log(e.name); // "TypeError"
  console.log(e.fileName); // "Scratchpad/1"
  console.log(e.lineNumber); // 2
  console.log(e.columnNumber); // 2
  console.log(e.stack); // "@Scratchpad/2:2:3\n"
}

```

### [Creating a TypeError](#creating%5Fa%5Ftypeerror)

```
try {
  throw new TypeError("Hello", "someFile.js", 10);
} catch (e) {
  console.log(e instanceof TypeError); // true
  console.log(e.message); // "Hello"
  console.log(e.name); // "TypeError"
  console.log(e.fileName); // "someFile.js"
  console.log(e.lineNumber); // 10
  console.log(e.columnNumber); // 0
  console.log(e.stack); // "@Scratchpad/2:2:9\n"
}

```
